cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.TYPES, cs.SE, cs.MS 

This paper is primarily focused on formalizing a programming language feature, namely path-dependent types, and proposes a new calculus to achieve this. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses soundness proofs and type safety, which are topics typically associated with cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.TYPES (Type Theory), respectively. Additionally, the paper mentions module systems and family polymorphism, which are relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software), respectively.
